                   "message":  "PROJECT-NAME-DISPLAY-FOLLOWUP: cover open-\u003ehook-\u003ename flow + distinct-name loader test + fix stale folder-name prose\n\nAudit P3 — the #279 (PROJECT-NAME-DISPLAY) loose ends. Tests + doc comments +\none test fixture only; no product behavior change, 0 Cargo.toml.\n\n1. Finding 4 (open-\u003ehook-\u003ename integration). The\n   SceneOpenHook::project_display_name plumbing in open_request.rs (ask the\n   binary-owned hook for the manifest name; thread it into\n   SaveSource::Project { name }) had no editor-shell test — the mock hook never\n   overrode it, and the existing display_name/snapshot tests build the variant by\n   hand. Add NamingSceneOpenHook (overrides project_display_name) and two tests\n   driving handle_open_request() on a .rge-project: the positive case asserts the\n   hook name reaches display_name (== \"My Cool Game\", != folder \"my-game\") and\n   the status snapshot; the negative case (default None hook) asserts the folder\n   fallback through the real open path.\n\n2. Finding 7 (distinct-name loader test). read_project_name_returns_golden_-\n   manifest_name asserts Some(\"simple-scene\") but the golden\u0027s FOLDER is also\n   simple-scene, so it cannot prove a manifest-field read vs a folder-name read.\n   Add a tracked fixture tests/fixtures/distinct-name-project/.rge-project whose\n   manifest name (\"Distinct Display Name\") differs from its folder, and a test\n   pinning that read_project_name returns the manifest name (and NOT the folder).\n   No new dependency (tempfile is not a workspace dep) and no golden-projects\n   coupling.\n\n3. Stale prose (doc comments). Post-#279 a .rge-project displays its MANIFEST\n   name (folder is the fallback), but several docs still said \"folder name\" as\n   the primary: window_title.rs, the editor-shell mod.rs save_status_snapshot\n   doc, and the canonical editor-state SaveStatusSnapshot type/field docs.\n   Corrected to \"manifest name (folder name when unnamed)\". The genuinely-\n   accurate fallback prose (main.rs, open_request.rs, save_source.rs, the test\n   comments) is left as-is.\n\n5 source files + 1 new test fixture, 0 Cargo.toml. Gate: VERIFY OK (7/7),\n10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
